.*.swp
*.log
*.orig
*.pyc
__pycache__/
.DS_Store

/*.pdf
/android/.gradle
/android/.kotlin
/fastlane/.bundle
/fastlane/.vendor
# fastlane writes a JUnit-style run report after every invocation; it is a
# build artifact (fresh timestamps each run), not a source file.
/fastlane/report.xml
/fastlane/metadata/android/*/images/.goutputstream-

/android/app/build
/android/app/src/main/res/raw/license_gpl3.md
/android/app/src/main/res/raw/license_apache2.md
/android/app/src/main/res/raw/license_gpl2.md
/android/app/src/main/res/raw*/usersguide.md
/android/guides.d
/android/build
/short
# Staged release artifacts: `make release` copies the signed AAB/APK and the SBOM
# here under their canonical <applicationId>_<versionCode>.<ext> names, and
# push-playstore / push-codeberg upload from here. Build outputs, never source.
/releases

# Release signing material and store upload credentials (Play + Codeberg) —
# SECRET, never commit. The committed templates are
# android/keystore.properties.example, ios/signing.properties.example and the
# SUPPLY_JSON_KEY note in fastlane/Appfile.
/android/keystore.properties
/ios/signing.properties
/fastlane/play-store-credentials.json
/fastlane/codeberg-credentials.txt
# App Store Connect API key (.p8) for the iOS deliver lanes — SECRET, downloads
# once and cannot be re-downloaded. Referenced via APP_STORE_CONNECT_API_KEY_*
# env vars (see fastlane/Fastfile, iOS block).
/fastlane/AuthKey_*.p8
# The App Store reviewer contact — a PERSON, reachable by phone, which is what
# Apple asks for and what a public repository should not answer. deliver reads
# these four as <key>.txt from fastlane/metadata/ios/review_information/ and
# sends them to App Store Connect; they are set up once per machine from the
# .txt.example files beside them, exactly like ios/signing.properties. The
# maintainer's name and address are already in every file header, so the phone
# number is the one genuinely new exposure — but the four are one contact, and
# splitting them would only invite the next person to commit the rest. The
# directory's notes.txt, demo_user.txt and demo_password.txt stay committed:
# they say the app has no login, which is true of the app, not of a person.
# tools/check-ios-metadata.py validates these when present, and push-appstore
# refuses to upload without them.
/fastlane/metadata/ios/review_information/first_name.txt
/fastlane/metadata/ios/review_information/last_name.txt
/fastlane/metadata/ios/review_information/email_address.txt
/fastlane/metadata/ios/review_information/phone_number.txt
# ignore iOS screenshots artifacts
/fastlane/screenshots/ios/screenshots.html

# Generated by 'make ios-version' from CHANGELOG.md and the Android versionCode
# (tools/gen-ios-version.py documents itself as git-ignored — this entry is what
# makes that true; it was missing until the 0.83.0 QA round). A committed copy
# would drift from the sources of truth.
/ios/Version.xcconfig

# Generated by 'xcodegen generate' from ios/project.yml ('make ios-project').
# docs/INSTALL-IOS.md: "The .xcodeproj is not committed" — you edit project.yml.
/ios/Potillus.xcodeproj

# Copied by 'make ios-project' from LICENSE.md — the same file Android copies
# into its res/raw/, so the two platforms show byte-identical text. Gitignored
# like Version.xcconfig: a copy in the tree would drift from the source. (Until
# 0.83.0 the source was COPYING.md, the output a combined copyright document, and
# a generator did the joining; it is one verbatim license per file now.)
/ios/Potillus/Resources/license_gpl3.md

# Generated by 'make ios-guides' from ios/docs/guide/*.md.in and the String
# Catalogue; one usersguide_<tag>.md per language, gitignored like license_gpl3.md.
/ios/Potillus/Resources/usersguide_*.md

# fastlane's own SnapshotHelper.swift, materialized by 'make screenshots-ios' from
# the installed fastlane (version-matched, never vendored) and picked up by
# xcodegen's PotillusUITests source glob. A committed copy would drift.
/ios/PotillusUITests/SnapshotHelper.swift
